> Gnocchi occupy the delicious middle ground between pasta and dumplings. These
> lovely little pillows are quite rich and filling, so we've included lots of
> veggies to balance them out. When our sales team tested this recipe it was
> their absolute favourite and we hope you enjoy it just as much!

Trim the @spring onion{2} then slice thinly. Roughly chop the
@flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all) and cut the
@premium tomato mix{125%g} in half. Trim the @cucumber{1} then quarter
lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Cut the
@British streaky bacon{120%g} into 1cm wide strips.

TIP: You can do this using scissors.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the
@gnocchi{300%g}. Fry, turning frequently, until crispy around the edges and
slightly browned, ~{8-9%minutes}. Once cooked, take the pan off the heat.

While the gnocchi is cooking, get started on the sauce! Heat a splash of oil in
another large frying pan on medium-high heat and add the bacon strips. Fry
until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-6%minutes}. Remove from the pan with a
#slotted spoon{} (try to leave most of the oil in the pan).

Reduce the heat to medium, add the spring onion, tomatoes and a grind of
@ground black pepper{grind} to the now empty pan you used for the bacon.
Cook for ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the @tomato puree{15%g} and cook for ~{1%minute}
more. Stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1/2%tsp} and the @water{100%ml}.
Simmer for ~{2%minutes}. Add the @baby spinach{125%g}. Cook until it wilts,
another ~{2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, squeeze the juice from the @lemon{1/2} into a #mixing bowl{} and add
the @honey{7.5%ml} and @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Season with a small pinch of
@salt{pinch} and a grind of pepper. Mix together with a #fork{}. Add half the
parsley to the bowl. Give everything a good toss.

Add the @crème fraîche{150%g}, bacon and the gnocchi to the sauce. Stir gently
and add half of the remaining parsley. Heat until everything is piping hot.
Divide the gnocchi between your plates, sprinkle over the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and the rest of the parsley. Serve with
the salad on the side and eat up! Enjoy!